And here is how much you learned

In week four, we discussed feedback.

You told us that you felt sensitive when receiving negative feedback,

...and happy when receiving positive feedback.

We then turned to learning about stress.

In week five, you reported feeling a lot of stress in your life right now, the primary source of it being classes.

We also talked about adversity and failure.

Although related, adversity and failure are different:

Adversity happens to us, whereas failure is something for which we are generally more responsible.

Perhaps that is why you said that failure had made you feel bad.

However, how we interpret stress and failure matters...

You said that you believe it is true that the effects of stress are negative and should be avoided,

...and that it is true that stress facilitates learning and growth.

Interestingly, research has found that people who believe that stress can facilitate learning and growth experience enhanced performance, well-being and health.

In week eight, we discussed interests.

We talked about states of extreme interest, or as Mihaly Csikszentmihalyi would call it, flow.

You said you had experienced flow when event-planning.

How do you feel when you are event-planning and get into the flow state?
